%I A397017 #6 Jun 17 2026 16:50:00
%S A397017 0,4,13,260,21914,6919179,7057377746
%N A397017 Number of directed self-avoiding cycles in the mod n square grid graph, reduced for symmetry (with rotations, reflections, and translations not counted as distinct).
%C A397017 Here a "mod n square grid graph" is a n X n graph with wrapping allowed, e.g., a path can make a 1 unit step between the left and the right edge (same row) or the top and the bottom edge (same column) of the graph.
%C A397017 Excludes 0 length cycles; including them increases each term by 1.
%e A397017 a(3) = 13 = A397016(3), all symmetric and count as 1 each both undirected and directed.
%e A397017 Nonsymmetric paths count as 2 each when directed, e.g.:
%e A397017   ..+--+--+     +..    .>+>>+>>+     +>.     .<+<<+<<+     +<.
%e A397017           |     |              v     ^               ^     v
%e A397017           +  +--+   ->         +  +>>+   and         +  +<<+
%e A397017           |  |                 v  ^                  ^  v
%e A397017           +--+                 +>>+                  +<<+
%Y A397017 Cf. A397016 (undirected), A396337 (directed paths), A390122 (wrapping disallowed).
%K A397017 nonn,walk,hard,more,new
%O A397017 1,2
%A A397017 _Charles L. Hohn_, Jun 13 2026
